# T5d bridge sequential gauntlet - 2026-05-22

Purpose: prove the workspace trigger bridge can run as a supervised loop and
process fresh target-agent triggers across easy, medium, hard, and extra-hard
diagnostic tasks without manual per-trigger activation.

Bridge command:

```text
node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs \
  --loop \
  --interval-ms 1000 \
  --limit 8 \
  --max-age-seconds 90 \
  --codex-timeout-ms 180000
```

The first attempted loop gauntlet exposed a bridge bug: pending triggers were
queried oldest-first and filtered by age locally, so stale backlog could hide
fresh triggers. The bridge was fixed to push `created_at >= cutoff` into the
REST query. A second safety fix treats terminal `*_ACK` and `*_BLOCKED`
messages as terminal triggers and completes them without launching a reverse
agent turn.

Validation:

```text
node --check scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs
exit 0

node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs --dry-run --limit 8 --max-age-seconds 900
result statuses included:
- would_complete_terminal for prior ACK trigger
- would_process for fresh non-terminal trigger
```

